        "created_at": "2025-11-01T14:35:39.376Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I have enabled Settings &gt; Accessibility &gt; Color and motion &gt; Remove animations. The intention of doing this is to “reduce movement on the screen”. However with this option enabled, filtering unread chats and clearing the filter by swiping down seems to result in more movement than it would otherwise.</p>\n<p>Generally, filtering unread chats and clearing the filter seems rather janky.</p>\n<p>The user interface seems to flicker when filtering unread chats. Clearing the filter seems very sensitive, a simple tap suffices. At times, trying to clear the filter by swiping down causes the filter to be removed and then applied directly afterwards, causing strong flickering and notably not the desired outcome :)</p>\n<p>Also it seems that when animations are <em>not</em> removed and unread chats are filtered, a button that says “Filtered by unread” is shown at the top that allows you to clear the filter. This button isn’t shown when animations are removed.</p>\n<p>This is version 7.62.3 on GrapheneOS 2025102800 (based on Android 16).</p>\n<p>Curious to hear if you can reproduce this behavior and whether or not you think it warrants opening an issue.</p>",
